<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="R" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Reed" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Reed,</orth> the hollow stem of several aquatic plants: <bibl n="shak. tmp 1.2.213" default="NO" valid="yes">Tp. I, 2, 213</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tmp 5.17.213" default="NO" valid="yes">V, 17</bibl> (<cit><quote>eaves of --s).</quote> <bibl n="shak. 1h4 1.3.105" default="NO" valid="yes">H4A I, 3, 105</bibl></cit>. <bibl n="shak. ant 2.7.13" default="NO" valid="yes">Ant. II, 7, 13</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. cym 4.2.267" default="NO" valid="yes">Cymb. IV, 2, 267</bibl>. Musical pipes made of it: <cit><quote>speak between the change of man and boy, with a r. voice,</quote> <bibl n="shak. mv 3.4.67" default="NO" valid="yes">Merch. III, 4, 67</bibl></cit>.

<pb n="952" />
